{{Infobox Russian town |en_name=Protvino |ru_name=Протвино |image_skyline=RIAN archive 501537 Protvino town.jpg |image_caption= |coordinates = {{coord|54|53|N|37|13|E|display=inline,title}} |map_label_position=left |image_coa=Coat of Arms of Protvino (Moscow oblast).png |coa_caption= |image_flag=Flag of Protvino (Moscow oblast).png |flag_caption= |anthem= |anthem_ref= |holiday= |holiday_ref= |federal_subject=[[Moscow Oblast]] |federal_subject_ref=<ref name="Ref1406" /> |adm_data_as_of=January 2013 |adm_city_jur=Protvino [[City of federal subject significance|Town Under Oblast Jurisdiction]] |adm_city_jur_ref=<ref name="Ref1406" /> |adm_ctr_of=Protvino Town Under Oblast Jurisdiction |adm_ctr_of_ref=<ref name="Ref1406" /> |inhabloc_cat=Town |inhabloc_cat_ref=<ref name="Ref1406" /> |mun_data_as_of=June 2011 |urban_okrug_jur=Protvino Urban Okrug |urban_okrug_jur_ref=<ref name="Ref795" /> |mun_admctr_of=Protvino Urban Okrug |mun_admctr_of_ref=<ref name="Ref795" /> |leader_title= |leader_title_ref= |leader_name= |leader_name_ref= |representative_body= |representative_body_ref= |area_of_what= |area_as_of= |area_km2= |area_km2_ref= |pop_2010census=37308 |pop_2010census_ref=<ref name="2010Census">{{ru-pop-ref|2010Census}}</ref> |pop_density= |pop_density_as_of= |pop_density_ref= |pop_latest= |pop_latest_date= |pop_latest_ref= |established_date= |established_title= |established_date_ref= |current_cat_date=1989 |current_cat_date_ref= |prev_name1= |prev_name1_date= |prev_name1_ref= |postal_codes= |postal_codes_ref= |dialing_codes= |dialing_codes_ref= |website=http://www.protvino.ru |website_ref= |date=February 2012 }} '''Protvino''' ({{lang-ru|Протвино́}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|town]] in [[Moscow Oblast]], [[Russia]], located about {{convert|100|km|sp=us}} south of [[Moscow]] and {{convert|15|km|sp=us}} west of [[Serpukhov]], on the left bank of the [[Protva River]]. Population: {{ru-census|p2010=37,308|p2002=36,175|p1989=34,520}}
==History== Construction of an [[urban-type settlement]] intended to house a large [[particle physics|high energy physics]] research laboratory started in 1958, and the [[Rosatom]] [[Institute for High Energy Physics]] was opened here in 1965. The institute is known for the 70 GeV [[particle accelerator|proton accelerator]] which was the largest in the world at the time it was launched in 1967, and other physics research. Town status was granted in 1989.{{citation needed|date=February 2012}} The [[UNK proton accelerator|UNK]] Collider was the last big planned particle accelerator.
Among the discoveries made at IHEP are that of [[antihelium]] and the Serpukhov cross-section effect.
==Administrative and municipal status== Within the [[subdivisions of Russia#Administrative divisions|framework of administrative divisions]], it is incorporated as '''Protvino [[City of federal subject significance|Town Under Oblast Jurisdiction]]'''—an administrative unit with the status equal to that of the [[administrative divisions of Moscow Oblast|districts]].<ref name="Ref1406">Law #11/2013-OZ</ref> As a [[subdivisions of Russia#Municipal divisions|municipal division]], Protvino Town Under Oblast Jurisdiction is incorporated as '''Protvino Urban Okrug'''.<ref name="Ref795">Law #159/2004-OZ</ref>
==Transport== [[File:Bus LiAZ 5292-60 in Protvino.jpg|thumb|LiAZ-5292 low-floor bus]] In the city the Protvino railroad station is located. Public transport is provided by buses.
