The '''Włodzimierz Trzebiatowski Institute of Low Temperature and Structure Research''' is a [[scientific]] [[institute]] in [[Wrocław]], [[Poland]]. It is named after [[Włodzimierz Trzebiatowski]], the [[Poland|Polish]] [[chemist]], [[physicist]] and [[mathematician]].

==Localization==
Until 1993 the Institute was placed at Gajowicka street and the Bishop Palace, that after the II World War was requisitioned by the  [[Polish People's Republic]] government. Currently the Institute is placed at Okólna street in Wrocław.

